comments:
Abolished 25.3.1883 and divided between the parishes of Bossington 
    and East Tytherley.
Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of King's Somborne.

On 25.3.1883 the part in Hampshire became 
    part of the parish of West Tytherley, so that thereafter West Dean was 
    entirely 
    in Wiltshire. See also Table 2, note (b).
